{"username":"CRubinson","name":"Claude Rubinson","image":"/static/uploads/user_photos/2014-09/rubinson-headshot.jpg","biography":"Claude Rubinson is an assistant professor of sociology at the University of Houston–Downtown where he teaches research methods, sociology of culture, and social inequality.  His research uses comparative-historical methods, including qualitative comparative analysis and other set-theoretic techniques, to examine how global political–economic instability affects art and aesthetics.  He has released a series of computer programs for conducting and visualizing set-theoretic social research.\r\n","website":"http://grundrisse.org/","social_handles":[]}